data.title: Henrietta & Samuel Barnett | Social Reformers | Blue Plaques
data.meta_description: Blue Plaque commemorating social reformers Henrietta and Samuel Barnett at Heath End House, Spaniards Road, Hampstead, London NW3 7JE, Borough of Camden.
data.text:
BARNETT, Samuel (1844-1913) & BARNETT, Dame Henrietta (1851-1936)

Plaque erected in 1983 by Greater London Council at Heath End House, Spaniards Road, Hampstead, London, NW3 7JE, London Borough of Camden

Profession

Social reformers

Category

Architecture and Building, Philanthropy and Reform

Inscription

DAME HENRIETTA BARNETT 1851-1936 Founder of Hampstead Garden Suburb and SAMUEL BARNETT 1844-1915 Social Reformer lived here

Material

Ceramic
